Durban - Just days after Community Safety and Liaison MEC Mxolisi Kaunda condemned illegal protests in the province, traffic on the N2 has been affected by yet another illegal protest. 
 
  
 
 
  On Thursday afternoon, at least two vehicles were set alight and others stoned during a protest on the N2 southbound just after the EB Cloete interchange. 
  Motorists have been urged to avoid the area. 
 
 
  
 
 
  
   







